  "text": "Machine-verified hardware/compiler/application stacks have been built before. Moore described a verified compiler for a \"high-level assembly language\" [CITATION_1] . Leinenbach et al. [CITATION_2] have built and proved a compiler for C0, a small C-like language, as part of a project to build machine-checked correctness proofs of source programs, Hoare Logic, compiler, micro-kernel, and RISC processor. These are both simple one-or two-pass nonoptimizing compilers.",
